MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

resume() now clears a settled merge/commit outcome when forwarding a live
(AWAITING_INPUT) session to createTurn, mirroring the revive path — so the bar
offers Merge afresh after "Resolve in session" instead of staying stuck on the
failed button once the agent rebases. An in-flight 'pending' is left alone for
its runner-api *-result to land.

The merge bar now only offers "Resolve in session" for a real 'conflict'; an
'error' (a precondition failure like a dirty main checkout that a rebase can't
fix) falls through to "Retry merge", with the detail in the panel below.
